.mon file parameters

[general]
name=name of the monitor (same of .mon file, without extension)
script=script to run with parameters (script must be inside of scripts subdirectory and must be executable)
message=Message to exhibit (accept %s for parameter substitution)
newmessage=New message to exhibit (in most cases, the same of "message").
check=numbers of seconds between checks
integer=0 or 1. If script returns should be used as an integer, use 1.
alwaywshowmessage=0 or 1. If script return message should always be send, use 1.
